      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KENNYWOULD (5) has been racing well in Victoria despite some tricky draws, winning from the back row last month at Kilmore and finishing runner-up in two of three starts since. Raced wide but stuck on when beaten only 2.2m last time. Can measure up. ALDEBARAN ZANE (7) is still a maiden but has the hoof on the till after finishing second in all three runs so far this prep. Led from wider and stuck on to finish 1.5 metres from the winner here last time. Race fit and could break through. PRINCESS DU FER (3) was fourth from this barrier last start at Bankstown and placed from wider here three back so is on the radar. KENNYS SON (1) broke last start but finished fourth in his previous two outings here and draws on the pegs.",
